Package: circlss
Type: Package
Title: Location-Scale Families for Circular Regression with 'mgcv'
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Ziwei", "Huang", email = "huang-ziwei@outlook.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Circular-response distributional families for the general family
    interface of 'mgcv', so that gam() fits penalized-spline regression models
    (GAM and GAMLSS) with an angular response and a separate linear predictor
    for each distribution parameter. The families span the von Mises (vmlss),
    projected normal (pnlss), wrapped Cauchy (wclss), wrapped normal (wnlss),
    cardioid (cardlss) and Cartwright power-of-cosine (cartlss) distributions,
    the Jones-Pewsey family (jplss) with its sine-skewed (ssjplss) and
    asymmetric (ajplss) forms, and the Kato-Jones (kjlss), flat-topped von
    Mises (vmftlss) and inverse Batschelet (ibslss) families that add skewness
    and peakedness. Weight-aware Gaussian (gausslss) and gamma (gammalss)
    location-scale families cover a linear response over circular covariates.
    Families with closed-form fourth-order derivatives use full Newton REML
    smoothing-parameter selection; the others supply first- and second-order
    derivatives and are fitted by the extended Fellner-Schall optimizer. The
    front-end circ_gam() wraps gam() for these families, and circ_mix() fits
    finite mixtures of them by EM.
